>[Question]
>how do i determine the square root of 1/2 
>
>[Difficulty]
>not sure why it is confusing, sometimes i think i know the answer 
>then I question it.
>
>[Thoughts]
>1/2x1/2=1/4

Thanks for writing to Ask Dr. Math, Joey!

Your thoughts are exactly right.  1/2 squared does equal 1/4.

To find the square root of 1/2, use

  sqrt(1/2) = sqrt(2/4) = sqrt(2)/sqrt(4) = sqrt(2)/2.

Feel free to reply if I can help further with this question.


